Here's the performance analysis for `Truncation.cs`. Since these methods are confirmed hot-path code (every displayed string, thousands of concurrent users), findings are elevated accordingly.

---

**Scan Execution Checklist:**

| Recipe | Hits |
|--------|------|
| IndexOf without StringComparison | 0 |
| Substring calls | 0 |
| Sync-over-async | 0 |
| `string.Split` | 1 |
| `.TrimEnd` (code, excl. comment) | 1 |
| `string.Join` | 2 |
| LINQ `.Take`/`.Skip` | 2 |
